  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Developing Water, Sanitation &amp; Hygiene Infrastructure  in Port-au-Prince</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-Implementation and monitoring of 15 water supply management structures on ACF interventions sites (interventions since January 2010)
-Monitoring of the quality of distributed water 
-Maintenance of sanitation infrastructures set up by ACF in 8 targeted districts
-Latrines emptying
-Hygiene promotion (communities, schools, restaurants, etc.), prevention on cholera, and community mobilization
-Creation, support and training of WASH infrastuctures management committees
-Water supply systems rehabilitation/construction for people living in the targeted districts
-Develop local chlorine production units and integration of income generating activities
-Distribution of water treatment kits
-Public latrines rehabilitation/construction
-Support to bayakous
-Establishment of a pilot project of ecological family latrines
-Implementation of waste management system&quot;</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improve the access to water, hygiene and sanitation for the populations affected by the earthquake of January 12, 2010, in 8 districts of Port au Prince.</narrative>
  </description>
